  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "+EzfE3rw7lkmzBO7D//jWdMwWAI=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "The buttons inside `DocumentToolbar` don't expose their own style props. They use hardcoded Tailwind classes:\n\n- **Undo/Redo/History/Close**: `border-gray-200 bg-white` with `Icon` children using `text-gray-900` or `text-gray-500`\n- **Export button**: Same pattern plus a `<span>` for the label\n- **Document name**: `<h1>` with `text-gray-500`\n\nTo customize them, use Tailwind arbitrary child selectors in the `className` prop:\n\n```tsx\n<DocumentToolbar\n  className={[\n    \"[&_button]:!bg-[#1e1e2e] [&_button]:!border-white/10\",\n    \"[&_button:hover]:!bg-[#313244]\",\n    \"[&_button_svg]:!text-gray-400\",\n    \"[&_span]:!text-gray-400\",\n    \"[&_h1]:!text-gray-400\",\n  ].join(\" \")}\n/>\n```\n\n### Selector reference\n| Selector | Targets |\n|----------|--------|\n| `[&_button]` | All buttons |\n| `[&_button_svg]` | Icons inside buttons |\n| `[&_button_span]` | Text labels (e.g. Export) |\n| `[&_h1]` | Document name |\n| `[&_button:hover]` | Button hover state |\n| `[&_button:disabled_svg]` | Disabled button icons |\n\nThis pattern works because Tailwind's arbitrary variant syntax lets you target descendants from a parent class string.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
    }
  },
